.jumbotron
  %h1 Blocipedia3
  %hr
  %p
    Wikis are a great way to collaborate on community-sourced content. Whether the wiki is for a hobby or work-related project, you will build an app that lets users create their own wikis and share them publicly or privately with other collaborators.

  %p
    %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-md{href: "/about", role: "button"} Learn more
    = link_to "Sign up", new_user_registration_path	, class: "btn btn-md btn-primary" if !current_user
    %br



- if current_user && current_user.standard?

  .well.bottom-well.rows.col-md-5
    = link_to "Upgrade to premium", new_charge_path, class: "btn btn-md btn-primary"
    %br
    %hr
      %ul
        %li Create private or public wikis
        %liAccess your private wikis
        %liAccess to all public wikis

- elsif current_user && current_user.premium?

  .well.bottom-well.rows.col-md-5
    = link_to "Downgrade back to standard", downgrade_charges_path, method: :post, class: "btn btn-md btn-primary", data: {confirm: 'Are you sure?'}
    %br
    %hr
    %ul
      %li If you have private wikis they will be converted to public wikis
      %li Create public wikis
      %li Access to all public wikis
